cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.SE, cs.LG

This paper discusses CoAlgebraic Logic Programming (CoALP), which is a dialect of Logic Programming. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also discusses termination and productivity analysis, which falls under the category of cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also mentions guarded lazy (co)recursion, which is related to functional theorem provers, and thus falls under the category of cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). The paper also discusses the comparison between lazy and eager execution, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE) and machine learning (cs.LG).
